  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "After setting up a forking project I run into this issue:\r\n\r\nafter a random amount of resets (sometimes on start up too) does hardhat face long waiting times, it can go from 100 ms up to 2 seconds per requests (this delay exists as long as the hardhat session is running)\r\nI then tried to send a lot of requests to this node directly but never faced such long delays.\r\n\r\nResults of testing:\r\n80% of tests did take around 5 seconds to go through which is fine\r\nbut around 20% took 20 to 40 seconds\r\nNo changes to the code or anything just random delay\r\nchanging nodes didnt help either",
